ğŸ—“ #OnThisDay - 1993
On 13 September 1993, the Sky Sports cameras were on Tyneside to capture Newcastle United's first ever LIVE midweek Premier League game at St. James' Park.
Striker Andrew Cole - better known then as Andy - opened the scoring before the visitors went in front courtesy of an Andy Sinton brace.
Cole equalised for Kevin Keegan's side with 14 minutes to play before Alex Mathie and Malcolm Allen sealed a fine comeback and a 4-2 win.
#125YearsUnited

The Magpies sat second in the Championship en route to the title.
